---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üìò WEEK 4 ‚Äì DAY 1 JavaScript | ES6+ Features

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üéØ Goal of Day 1

‚úî Understand **modern JavaScript (ES6+)**
‚úî Learn **cleaner & shorter syntax**
‚úî Write **professional, interview-ready JS code**

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üåê What is ES6+?

**ES6 (ECMAScript 2015)** introduced modern features to JavaScript.
**ES6+** means ES6 and all later updates.

üìå Makes JavaScript:

* Cleaner
* Faster
* Easier to maintain
* More powerful

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üîë `let` and `const`

`let`

```js
let count = 10;
count = 20;
```

`const` (Recommended ‚≠ê)

```js
const PI = 3.14;
```

üìå Block-scoped
üìå Avoid `var`

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üÜö var vs let vs const (Quick Recap)

| Feature     | var      | let   | const |
| ----------- | -------- | ----- | ----- |
| Scope       | Function | Block | Block |
| Reassign    | ‚úÖ       | ‚úÖ   | ‚ùå    |
| Recommended | ‚ùå       | ‚úÖ   | ‚≠ê    |

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

‚ö° Arrow Functions

Normal Function

```js
function add(a, b) {
  return a + b;
}
```

Arrow Function

```js
const add = (a, b) => a + b;
```

üìå Short syntax
üìå Used everywhere in modern JS

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üß© Template Literals

Used for **string interpolation**.

```js
let name = "Saakshi";
console.log(`Hello ${name}`);
```

üìå Use backticks `` ` ``
üìå Cleaner than `+`

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üì¶ Destructuring

Array Destructuring

```js
let [a, b] = [10, 20];
```

Object Destructuring

```js
let user = { name: "Saakshi", age: 21 };
let { name, age } = user;
```

üìå Makes code short & readable

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üåü Spread Operator (`...`)

Copy Array

```js
let arr1 = [1, 2];
let arr2 = [...arr1, 3, 4];
```

 Copy Object

```js
let user2 = { ...user, city: "Delhi" };
```

üìå Avoids mutation

---

üì• Rest Operator (`...`)

Used in function parameters.

```js
function sum(...numbers) {
  return numbers.reduce((a, b) => a + b);
}
```

---

üß† Default Parameters

```js
function greet(name = "User") {
  console.log(`Hello ${name}`);
}
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üîÅ Enhanced Object Literals

```js
let name = "Saakshi";

let user = {
  name,
  greet() {
    console.log("Hello");
  }
};
```

üìå No need to repeat keys

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üìö New Array Methods (ES6+)

map()

```js
nums.map(n => n * 2);
```

filter()

```js
nums.filter(n => n > 5);
```

find()

```js
nums.find(n => n === 3);
```

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üß© for...of Loop

```js
for (let item of arr) {
  console.log(item);
}
```

üìå Cleaner than `for` loop

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üîê Optional Chaining (`?.`)

Prevents runtime errors.

```js
user?.address?.city;
```

üìå Returns `undefined` instead of error

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üß™ Nullish Coalescing (`??`)

```js
let value = input ?? "Default";
```

üìå Works only for `null` or `undefined`

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

‚è≥ Promises (Intro)

Used for **async operations**.

```js
const promise = new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
  resolve("Success");
});
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

‚ö° async / await (Modern Async)

```js
async function fetchData() {
  let result = await fetch(url);
}
```

üìå Cleaner than `.then()`

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üì¶ Modules (import / export)

export

```js
export function add(a, b) {
  return a + b;
}
```

import

```js
import { add } from "./file.js";
```

üìå Used in React, Node, Next.js

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

‚ùå Common ES6 Mistakes

* Mixing `var` with `let`
* Forgetting `return` in arrow functions
* Mutating arrays instead of spreading
* Not using template literals

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üí° Best Practices

* Use `const` by default
* Prefer arrow functions
* Use destructuring
* Use spread operator
* Write readable modern JS

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

‚úÖ DAY-1 Summary (Week-4)

* ES6 overview
* let & const
* Arrow functions
* Template literals
* Destructuring
* Spread & rest
* Modern loops
* Async basics
